cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CY 

This paper deals with the evaluation of distributional semantic models, which are commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) tasks such as text classification, sentiment analysis, and machine translation. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). 

The paper also discusses the use of word vectors, which are a type of machine learning model commonly used in NLP. This makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. 

The hypothesis being tested involves the correlation between embeddings and eye movement data, which is a type of neuro-cognitive resource. This suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) could also be relevant sub-categories. 

Finally, the paper deals with experiments on English and Russian datasets, which suggests that cs.CY (Computers and Society) could be a less likely but still possible sub-category.
